ad.title: Enthusiastic Babysitter Available in Strasbourg: Meet Aswini
ad.content:
Hello,
My name is Aswini, and I am a 24-year-old student currently pursuing the Grand Ecole program at EM Strasbourg Business School. I am very fluent in English and a beginner in French. While I'm dedicated to my studies, I also have a passion for taking care of children. 
I have taken care of my nephew since his birth, and he is now a lively 5-year-old. This experience has equipped me with the skills and patience required to handle the joys and challenges that come with childcare.
My schedule is flexible, making it easier for you to plan your childcare needs. I am available on Thursday, Friday, Saturday, and Sunday, making weekends a breeze for you. Additionally, I am free on Wednesday after 18:00, and I have availability on Monday mornings. This allows you to have peace of mind knowing that I can accommodate your requirements.
I consider myself a friendly, calm, and patient individual. I understand the importance of creating a safe and nurturing environment for children, where they can learn and grow. I take pride in my ability to connect with children, making them feel comfortable and secure in my presence. Whether it's playtime, homework help, or bedtime stories, I'm here to ensure that your child feels loved and cared for.
f you are looking for a responsible and caring babysitter in Strasbourg, I would be thrilled to assist you. Please feel free to contact me at your convenience. I'm more than happy to discuss your specific needs and provide you with any additional information you may require.

ad.title: Garde occasionnelle
ad.content:

Durant six mois, j'ai suivi une formation d'Assistante De Vie aux Familles (ADVF) qui comprend trois domaines de compétences professionnelles dont celui de relayer les parents dans la prise en charge des enfants à domicile.
